inessinsider.com%2Ftech-podcasts-silicon-valley-ideology-andreessen-horowitz-calacanis-palihapitiya-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAll-In%26quot%3B%20podcast%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20industry%20veterans%20Chamath%20Palihapitiya%2C%20Jason%20Calacanis%2C%20David%20Sacks%2C%20and%20Friedberg%20cover%20all%20things%20economy%2C%20tech%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20poker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20summit%20included%20a%20rare%20live%20appearance%20by%20Brin%2C%20who%20discussed%20the%20%26quot%3Bmind%20blowing%26quot%3B%20advancement%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20computer%20scientist%2C%20I've%20never%20seen%20anything%20as%20exciting%20as%20all%20of%20the%20progress%20that's%20happened%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Brin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsergey-brin-career-life-education%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20said%20he's%20spending%20nearly%20every%20day%20at%20Google%20these%20days%2C%20praised%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-gemini-bard%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI's%3C%2Fa%3E%20multi-faceted%20abilities%2C%20specifically%20with%20regard%20to%20programming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWriting%20code%20from%20scratch%20feels%20really%20hard%20compared%20to%20just%20asking%20the%20AI%20to%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Brin%20said%20to%20laughs%20from%20the%20audience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrin%20said%20he%20was%20curious%20about%20how%20good%20Google's%20AI%20model%20would%20be%20at%20Sudoku.%20As%20an%20experiment%2C%20Brin%20had%20the%20model%20write%20code%20that%20would%20automatically%20generate%20versions%20of%20the%20puzzle.%20The%20test%20sparked%20some%20debate%20among%20Google%20engineers%2C%20Brin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20he%20came%20back%20just%2030%20minutes%20later%2C%20the%20model%20had%20successfully%20done%20its%20job%2C%20Brin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20kind%20of%20impressed%2C%26quot%3B%20Brin%20said%20of%20the%20engineers.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20they%20don't%20honestly%20use%20the%20AI%20tools%20for%20their%20own%20coding%20as%20much%20as%20I%20think%20they%20ought%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrin%2C%20later%20in%20the%20conversation%2C%20also%20said%20that%20Google%20had%20been%20too%20%26quot%3Btimid%26quot%3B%20to%20release%20its%20early%20language%20models%20because%20they%20made%20mistakes%20and%20said%20%26quot%3Bembarrassing%20things.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20AI's%20programming%20capabilities%2C%20Brin%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20have%20some%20embarrassments%20and%20take%20some%20risks%2C%20and%20I%20think%20we've%20gotten%20better%20at%20that%2C%20and%20well%2C%20you%20guys%20have%20probably%20seen%20some%20of%20our%20embarrassments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20approach%20to%20utilizing%20AI%20hasn't%20stopped%20its%20employees%20from%20getting%20poached%20as%20the%20AI%20talent%20war%20heats%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20reported%20in%20June%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-google-poaching-staff-ai-talent-war-sam-altman-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20had%20hired%20at%20least%2044%20ex-Googlers%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year%20alone%2C%20about%20half%20of%20whom%20were%20engineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20has%20taken%20a%20proactive%20approach%20in%20trying%20to%20stay%20AI-relevant.%20As%20search%20competition%20continues%20to%20heat%20up%2C%20Google%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-overviews-search-engine-new-openai-searchgpt-competition-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupdated%20its%20AI%20Overviews%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20a%20feature%20that%20produces%20AI-generated%20answers%20in%20response%20to