20elected%20governments.%20Today%2C%20it%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%2C%20feared%20and%20unpopular%20institutions%20in%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20seem%20hard%20to%20explain%20how%20an%20army%20that%20was%20so%20badly%20humiliated%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20lost%20one%20big%20chunk%20of%20the%20country%20and%20was%20made%20to%20surrender%20en%20masse%20to%20its%20arch-rival%20in%201971%2C%20went%20on%20to%20become%20the%20country's%20main%20power%20centre.%20But%2C%20there%20is%20an%20explanation%3A%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20owes%20a%20lot%20to%20the%20US%20and%20China%2C%20both%20of%20which%20helped%20in%20rebuilding%20it.%20It%20also%20got%20a%20new%20fillip%20under%20General%20Zia%2C%20who%20began%20to%20Islamise%20the%20country%20and%20the%20armed%20forces.%20It%20got%20a%20boost%20when%20nuclear%20tests%20were%20conducted%2C%20and%20another%20shot%20in%20the%20arm%20when%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20invaded%20Afghanistan%20in%201979.%20The%20US%20poured%20arms%20and%20money%20into%20Pakistan%20and%20bolstered%20the%20army's%20capabilities%2C%20supplying%20its%20air%20force%20with%20F16%20fighter%20jets.%20Following%209%2F11%2C%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20even%20joined%20the%20US-led%20global%20war%20on%20terror.%20For%20years%2C%20America%20paid%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20%242%20billion%20a%20year%20for%20being%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20global%20war%20on%20terrorism%20and%20supporting%20its%20operations%20and%20logistics%20in%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Vice-Like%20Grip%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20practice%2C%20much%20of%20Pakistan's%20security%20issues%20and%20foreign%20affairs%20are%20reported%20to%20be%20shaped%20not%20in%20the%20capital%20Islamabad%20but%20at%20the%20General%20Headquarters%20in%20Rawalpindi%2C%20where%20the%20Chief%20of%20Army%20Staff%20(COAS)%20plays%20the%20role%20of%20a%20kingmaker.%20The%20military%20has%20significant%20economic%20interests%2C%20with%20control%20over%20large%20sectors%20of%20real%20estate%2C%20agriculture%2C%20corporations%20and%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan's%20current%20political%20turmoil%20was%20triggered%20when%20Imran%20Khan%2C%20who%20came%20to%20power%20with%20the%20army's%20support%2C%20later%20began%20to%20defy%20its%20authority.%20Many%20believe%20that%20if%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20have%20tepid%20bilateral%20relations%20today%2C%20it%20is%20because%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20appears%20reluctant%20to%20allow%20civilian%20governments%20to%20build%20a%20warm%20relationship%20with%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20considered%20view%20in%20the%20West%20is%20that%20the%20military%20is%20the%20main%20institution%20that%20holds%20Pakistan%20together.%20A%20few%20foreign%20policy%20think%20tank%20people%20I%20have%20interacted%20with%20in%20recent%20weeks%20are%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20for%20all%20its%20faults%2C%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20is%20the%20one%20institution%20that%20can%20take%20on%20the%20forces%20endangering%20the%20country's%20future.%20They%20argue%20that%20the%20West%20needs%20a%20disciplined%20institution%20like%20the%20Pakistan%20military%20that%20can%20safeguard%20the%20big%20nuclear%20stockpile%20that%20Islamabad%20has%20amassed.%20They%20urge%20the%20military%20to%20mend%20relations%20with%20India%20and%20hope%20that%20it%20will%20respond%20positively%20because%20a%20disintegrated%20Pakistan%2C%20the%20argument%20goes%2C%20will%20create%20havoc%20in%20the%20region%2C%20which%20will%20severely%20affect%20India%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDemocratic%20Rule%20Is%20In%20Everyone's%20Interest%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%2C%20however%2C%20think%20this%20is%20a%20myopic%20view.%20The%20West%20should%20try%20to%20help%20strengthen%20political%20parties%20and%20push%20for%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20autonomy%20of%20national%20institutions.%20The%20restoration%20of%20true%20democracy%20should%20be%20everyone's%20objective.%20It%20will%20be%20easier%20for%20any%20country%2C%20more%20particularly%20a%20democratic%20India%2C%20to%20deal%20with%20an%20elected%20civilian%20government%2C%20with%20no%20direct%20or%20indirect%20interference%20by%20the%20Pakistani%20army.%20Former%20prime%20ministers%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20and%20Benazir%20Bhutto%20felt%20immense%20pressure%20from%20the%20army%20when%20they%20tried%20to%20initiate%20dialogues%20with%20India.%20During%20the%20two%20full-scale%20wars%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20in%201965%20and%201971%2C%20the%20country%20was%20ruled%20by%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kargil%20War%20in%201999%20is%20widely%20seen%20as%20an%20attempt%20by%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20to%20undermine%20the%20civilian%20government's%20efforts%20to%20establish%20peace%20with%20India.%20The%20war%20highlighted%20the%20tensions%20between%20Pakistan's%20civilian%20and%20military%20leadership%20and%20the%20army's%20willingness%20to%20pursue%20its%20own%20agenda%2C%20even%20if%20it%20meant%20undermining%20the%20country's%20democratic%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Root%20Cause%20Of%20Terrorism%20In%20India%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20public%20view%20in%20India%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20that%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20terrorism%20here%20is%20the%20Pakistan%20army.%20The%20Indian%20government%20has%20largely%20been%20sceptical%20of%20a%20dialogue%20with%20Pakistan%2C%20which%20it%20accuses%20of%20exporting%20terrorism%20to%20its%20territories.%20It%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20callous%20for%20the%20West%20to%20disregard%20the%20fact%20that%20over%20the%20past%20four%20decades%2C%20India%20has%20been%20at%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20terrorism%2C%20which%2C%20India%20believes%2C%20is%20being%20perpetuated%20by%20Pakistan.%20India%20has%20shared%20evidence%20too%20with%20its%20Western%20allies%20and%20even%20with%20Pakistan%2C%20which%20reveals%20how%20the%20Inter-Services%20Intelligence%20(ISI)%20of%20Pakistan's%20army%20plans%20and%20trains%20young%20boys%20to%20commit%20acts%20of%20terrorism%20in%20India.%20Pakistan%2C%20expectedly%2C%20has%20always%20denied%20the%20allegations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20denial%20carries%20little%20weight.%20On%20May%2016%2C%202011%2C%20David%20Coleman%20Headley%2C%20one%20of%20the%20main%20planners%20of%20the%20Mumbai%20terror%20attack%2C%20appeared%20in%20a%20federal%20court%20in%20Chicago%20and%20revealed%20how%20two%20ISI%20officers%20were%20present%20during%20the%20planning%20and%20training%20stages%20of%20the%20attack.%20I%20was%20present%20in%20the%20courtroom%20when%20he%20narrated%20this.%20In%20his%20long%20testimony%2C%20he%20gave%20graphic%20details%20of%20what%20instructions%20he%20got%20from%20the%20ISI%20men%20and%20which%20places%20in%20Mumbai%20he%20was%20told%20to%20target.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%2010%20heavily%20armed%20terrorists%20who%20attacked%20Mumbai%20had%20come%20from%20Pakistan.%20This%20is%20a%20well-known%20fact%20that%20none%20should%20dispute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETerror%20Camps%20And%20Training%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20have%20met%20scores%20of%20militants%20during%20my%20long%20years%20in%20reporting%2C%20who%20have%20shared%20with%20me%20details%20of%20their%20training%20routines%20in%20camps%20in%20and%20around%20Muzaffarabad.%20I%20have%20met%20a%20few%20journalists%20from%20Pakistan%20who%20have%20visited%20these%20camps%2C%20organised%20by%20authorities%20and%20Islamist%20outfits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20civilian%20governments%20in%20Pakistan%20have%20largely%20not%20been%20averse%20to%20being%20friends%20with%20India.%20The%20people%2C%20too%2C%20admire%20the%20progress%20India%20has%20made.%20The%20two%20countries%20have%20had%20a%20history%20of%20Track-II%20diplomacy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Pakistan%20army's%20obsession%20with%20Kashmir%20and%20its%20desire%20for%20parity%20with%20India%20has%20led%20to%20hostilities%20and%20has%20hindered%20regional%20peace%20and%20stability.%20And%20thus%2C%20peaceful%20negotiations%20to%20normalise%20bilateral%20relations%20can%20be%20successful%20only%20if%20the%20army's%20influence%20is%20weakened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20will%20have%20to%20take%20some%20steps%20too%20to%20achieve%20this%20non-combatant%20objective%20-%20something%20that%20will%20ultimately%20contribute%20to%20overall%20peace%20and%20stability%20in%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent.%20India%20will%20have%20to%20support%20Pakistan's%20civilian%20leadership%20and%20democratic%20forces%20that%20seek%20to%20reduce%20the%20army's%20influence%20over%20the%20country's%20politics.%20This%20will%20include%20taking%20a%20stand%20against%20the%20Pakistan%20Army's%20human%20rights%20abuses%20in%20Kashmir%20and%20Balochistan%20and%20restructuring%20ties%20with%20countries%20like%20Iran%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20which%20share%20concerns%20about%20Pakistan's%20military%20and%20its%20adventurism.%20India%20could%20also%20do%20more%20to%20invest%20in%20strategic%20communications%20to%20counter%20the%20Pakistan%20army's%20propaganda%20and%20disinformation%20campaigns.%20By%20pursuing%20these%20strategies%2C%20India%20can%20create%20an%20environment%20that%20undermines%20the%20Pakistan%20army's%20dominance%20and%20creates%20space%20for%20more%20constructive%20engagement%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeakening%20The%20Pak%20Army%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20strategies%20are%20not%20new.%20During%20the%201971%20Bangladesh%20Liberation%20War%2C%20India%20supported%20Mukti%20Bahini%20to%20weaken%20the%20Pakistani%20military's%20control%20over%20East%20Pakistan%20(now%20Bangladesh).%20Several%20big%20powers%20adopt%20these%20strategies.%20The%20US%20has%20conducted%20cyber%20operations%20and%20supported%20opposition%20groups%20to%20weaken%20the%20Revolutionary%20Guards's%20influence%20in%20Iran%2C%20while%20Israel%20has%20taken%20similar%20actions%20against%20both%20the%20Iranian%20Revolutionary%20Guard%20and%20Lebanon's%20Hezbollah.%20Again%2C%20during%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20the%20US%20engaged%20in%20a%20strategy%20of%20economic%20pressure%2C%20diplomatic%20isolation%20and%20ideological%20competition%20to%20weaken%20the%20Soviet%20military.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaudi%20Arabia's%20military%20is%20an%20example%20of%20how%20things%20can%20go%20horribly%20wrong%20if%20done%20in%20haste.%20Its%20military%20operations%20and%20support%20for%20opposition%20groups%20with%20a%20view%20to%20weakening%20the%20Houthi%20rebels'%20control%20over%20Yemen%20have%20not%20yielded%20any%20success%20at%20all.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20will%20thus%20have%20to%20pursue%20these%20strategies%20tactfully%2C%20without%20seeming%20to%20be%20interfering%20in%20Pakistan's%20internal%20affairs.%20Kashmir%20will%20always%20remain%20an%20issue%20for%20the%20two%20countries%2C%20%C2%A0but%20it's%20possible%20to%20agree%20to%20work%20on%20other%20bilateral%20issues%20to%20first%20normalise%20relations.%20If%20there%20is%20political%20will%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20border%20and%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20takes%20a%20backseat%2C%20peace%20may%20not%20be%20so%20unachievable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726046580000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Frg1r6j2o_pakistan_625x300_11_September_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-pakistan-peace-is-possible-only-if-pak-army-takes-a-back-seat-6540120%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20have%20tepid%20bilateral%20relations%20today%2C%20it%20is%20because%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20appears%20reluctant%20to%20allow%20civilian%20governments%20