%20mango%20pickle.%20Rather%20than%20making%20the%20food%20herself%2C%20Reshma%20decided%20to%20create%20a%20platform%20where%20people%20like%20her%20mother%20and%20aunt%20could%20sell%20their%20dishes%20directly.%20This%20would%20help%20them%20become%20financially%20independent%20and%20turn%20their%20passion%20into%20a%20thriving%20business.%20For%20customers%2C%20it%20offers%20a%20way%20to%20enjoy%20the%20local%20delicacies%20they%20crave!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarted%20in%202023%2C%20Tocco%20now%20has%20over%2016%20chefs%2C%20both%20men%20and%20women%2C%20mostly%20in%20their%2050s%2C%20whose%20dreams%20have%20been%20given%20wings%20through%20the%20platform!%20Starting%20with%20just%20Rs%205%2C000%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F355942%2Forganic-masala-spices-in-coimbatore-tamil-nadu-iniya-organics-business-podis-health-mixes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebootstrapped%20business%20%3C%2Fa%3Eachieved%20a%20turnover%20of%20over%20Rs%201%20crore%20in%20the%20current%20year.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20how%20Reshma%20is%20empowering%20those%20with%20a%20lifelong%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EPacking%20childhood%20memories%20in%20a%20box%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReshma%2C%20an%20engineer%2C%20moved%20to%20Mumbai%20in%202012%20for%20work.%20She%20worked%20in%20healthcare%20startups%20for%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20gaining%20first-hand%20experience%20in%20healthcare%20and%20health%20tech.%20Joining%20these%20startups%20from%20their%20infancy%2C%20she%20had%20a%20front-row%20understanding%20of%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20scale%20a%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusy%20with%20work%2C%20a%20huge%20portion%20of%20her%2020s%20was%20spent%20eating%20out%20or%20cooking%20for%20herself.%20She%20constantly%20craved%20a%20good%20home-cooked%20meal%2C%20just%20like%20the%20ones%20her%20mother%20used%20to%20make.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20missed%20my%20roots%20and%20the%20food%20I%20grew%20up%20eating.%20Every%20time%20I%20visited%20home%20in%20Kochi%2C%20I%20brought%20back%20staples%20like%20banana%20chips%2C%20pickles%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Epodis%20%3C%2Fem%3E(spice%20powders)%2C%20which%20made%20cooking%20a%20meal%20very%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201280px)%20100vw%2C%201280px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FTocco-women-1726037821.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20women%20of%20Tocco%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FTocco-women-1726037821.jpeg%201280w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FTocco-women-1726037821-300x168.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FTocco-women-1726037821-500x280.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FTocco-women-1726037821-768x431.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FTocco-women-1726037821-150x84.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-365471%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22718%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20women%20of%20Tocco.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20find%20a%20consistent%20and%20convenient%20supply%20of%20food%20that%20reminded%20me%20of%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20Reshma%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20hectic%20schedule%20coupled%20with%20late%20nights%20led%20to%20lots%20of%20restaurant%20meals.%20A%20few%20years%20later%2C%20Reshma%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20PCOS%20(Polycystic%20Ovary%20Syndrome).%20This%20diagnosis%20triggered%20her%20search%20for%20healthier%2C%20authentic%2C%20home-cooked%20regional%20food.%20Unfortunately%2C%20she%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20find%20a